<html>
<head>
<title>ToMar Games: Birthday Number</title>
<script language="javascript">
function calc()
{	
	var mm = document.test.month.selectedIndex + 1;
	var dd = document.test.day.selectedIndex + 1;
	var yyyy = 2000 - document.test.year.selectedIndex;
	var birthday = mm + "/" + dd + "/" + yyyy;
	var n = parseInt(mm) + parseInt(dd) + parseInt(yyyy);
    	while	(n > 9)
	{
		numchar = "" + n;
		n = 0;
		for	(var i = 0; i < numchar.length; i++)
		{
			n += parseInt(numchar.substring(i,i+1));
		}
	}	
	alert("For your birthday, " + birthday + ", your Birthday Number is #"
		 + n + ". Read below to see what that means...");
}
</script>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFCCBB" text="#009999">
<p align="center"><font size="6" face="ms sans serif">Your Birthday Number</font></p>
<p align="left"><font size="4" face="ms sans serif" color="#000080">
Your birthdate describes who you are, what you are good at, and what your inborn abilities are.
It also points to what you have to learn, and the challenges you are facing. 
<br><br>
Your birthday number
is calculated by adding the numbers of your birthday over and over again, until only one digit is
left. For example, if you were born on February 15, 1956, it would be 2 + 15 + 1956 = 1973, then
1 + 9 + 7 + 3 = 20, then 2 + 0 = 2. So your birthday number would be 2.
<br><br>
Your birthday number will never prevent you from being anything you want, it will just color
your choices differently.
<br><br>
<form method="post" name="test">
We'll do the math for you if you enter your birthdate below.
<br><br>
Month:
<select size=1 name="month">
<script language="javascript">
	for	(var i = 1; i < 13; i++)
	{
		document.write("<option>" + i + "</option>");
	}
</script>
</select>
Day:
<select size=1 name="day">
<script language="javascript">
	for	(var i = 1; i < 32; i++)
	{
		document.write("<option>" + i + "</option>");
	}
</script>
</select>
Year:
<select size=1 name="year">
<script language="javascript">
	for	(var i = 2000; i > 1910; i--)
	{
		document.write("<option>" + i + "</option>");
	}
</script>
</select>
<br><br>
<input name="x" type="button" value="Calculate Birthday Number" onClick="calc()">
</form>

<p align="center"><font size="5" face="ms sans serif" color="#000080">
What Your Birthday Number Means
</font></p>
<p align="left"><font size="3" face="ms sans serif" color="#000080">
<b>#1 - The Originator</b><br>
You are an original. Coming up with new ideas and executing them
is natural to you. Having things your own way also seems natural, but
may get you
labeled as stubborn and arrogant. You are extremely honest, so
you may have to work extra hard on diplomacy skills. You like to take the
initiative and are probably a leader or a boss, as you like to be the
best. Being self-employed is a good choice for you. Lesson to learn: Others' 
ideas might be just as good or better than your own, so stay open-minded.
<br><br>
<p align="left"><font size="3" face="ms sans serif" color="#002020">
<b>Famous #1's:</b><br>
Tom Hanks, Robert Redford, Hulk Hogan, Carol Burnett, Wynonna Judd,
Nancy Reagan, Raquel Welch
<br><br>
<p align="left"><font size="3" face="ms sans serif" color="#000080">
<b>#2 - The Peacemaker</b><br>
You are a born diplomat. You are aware of others' needs and moods,
and often think of others before yourself. Naturally analytical and 
intuitive, you don't like to be alone. Friendship and companionship
are very important to you, and can lead you to be successful in life, 
but you would rather be alone than in an uncomfortable relationship. 
Being naturally shy, you should learn to boost your self-esteem and 
express yourself freely.  Don't put things off; seize the moment.
<br><br>
<p align="left"><font size="3" face="ms sans serif" color="#002020">
<b>Famous #2's:</b><br>
President Bill Clinton, Madonna, Whoopie Goldberg, Thomas Edison,
Wofgang Amadeus Mozart
<br><br>
<p align="left"><font size="3" face="ms sans serif" color="#000080">
<b>#3 - The Life of the Party</b><br>
You are an idealist. You are very creative, social, charming, romantic,
 and easygoing. You start many things, but don't always see them through.
You like others to be happy, and will go to great lengths to keep them
that way. You are very popular and idealistic. You may need to learn to
see the world from a more realistic point of view.
<br><br>
<p align="left"><font size="3" face="ms sans serif" color="#002020">
