You are sensible and traditional. You like order and routine. You only
act when you fully understand what you are expected to do. You like 
getting your hands dirty and working hard. You are attracted to the
outdoors, and you feel an affinity with nature. You are prepared to 
wait for the things you want; you could be considered to be stubborn 
and persistent. One thing you could work on is your flexibility (or
lack of it), and you should always remember to be nice to yourself. 
<br><br>
<p align="left"><font size="3" face="ms sans serif" color="#002020">
<b>Famous #4's:</b><br>
Neil Diamond, Margaret Thatcher, Arnold Schwarzenegger, Tina Turner,
Paul Hogan, Oprah Winfrey
<br><br>
<p align="left"><font size="3" face="ms sans serif" color="#000080">
<b>#5 - The Non-Conformist</b><br>
You are an explorer. Your natural curiosity, risk taking, and
enthusiasm often land you in hot water. You need diversity; you don't
like to be stuck in a rut. The whole world is your school, and you see
a learning possibility in every situation. Your questions never stop. 
You should learn to look before you take action, and make sure you have
all the facts before you jump to conclusions.
<br><br>
<p align="left"><font size="3" face="ms sans serif" color="#002020">
<b>Famous #5's:</b><br>
Abraham Lincoln, Charlotte Bronte, Jessica Walter, Vincent van Gogh,
Bette Midler, Helen Keller
<br><br>
<p align="left"><font size="3" face="ms sans serif" color="#000080">
<b>#6 - The Romantic</b><br>
You are idealistic, and you need to feel useful in order to be happy.
A strong family connection is important to you. Your emotions often
influence your decisions. You have a strong urge to take care of and 
help others. You are very loyal; you take friendship very seriously.
You like art and/or music, and would probably make a good teacher.
You need to work on your ability to distinguish between the things you
can and cannot change. 
<p align="left"><font size="3" face="ms sans serif" color="#002020">
<b>Famous #6's:</b><br>
Albert Einstein, Jane Seymour, John Denver, Meryl Streep, Christopher
